  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db4\u0dc4 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Five and a half lakhs collected on the road will be handed over to the owner",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Tissamaharama police stated that the conductor and driver of a Hakmana Tissamaharama bus found and handed over Rs.",
        "Thus the wallet was picked up by Mr. TG Bandulasena, a resident of Barawakumbuka, who works at the Tangalle depot, and Mr. H. M. Tissamaharama Police stated that the driver is a resident of Ambalantota area, Kulasiri.",
        "The manager of a hotel in Tissamaharama has complained to the Tissamaharama police that the wallet fell with the mobile phone when he was taking the money to deposit in a bank.",
        "Later, he contacted the mobile phone and said that the wallet was picked up near Tissamaharama bus stand and that the bus was going to Tangalle area and that he should come to Tangalle depot and collect the wallet.",
        "Accordingly, the Tissamaharama police went to the Tangalle depot with the owner and handed over the wallet to the owner in the presence of the police in a short period of three hours, said the Tissamaharama police."
      ],
